%I A393943 #25 Mar 13 2026 23:19:35
%S A393943 1,-2,1,12,-9,2,-24,22,-8,1,720,-750,350,-75,6,-1440,1644,-900,255,
%T A393943 -36,2,60480,-74088,45472,-15435,2940,-294,12,-120960,156816,-105056,
%U A393943 40614,-9408,1288,-96,3,3628800,-4931280,3543720,-1513890,404082,-68040,7020,-405,10
%N A393943 Triangle read by rows: T(n, k) is the coefficient of x^k in the unique (up to scale) degree-n polynomial P_n(x) with P_n(0) = 0 whose derivative P_n'(x) has zeros exactly at 1, 2, ..., n - 1.
%C A393943 Coefficients are normalized so that T(n, n) > 0 and the gcd of the nonconstant coefficients is 1; i.e., gcd(T(n, 1), ..., T(n, n)) = 1.
%C A393943 For n = 1, the set {1, ..., n - 1} is empty; with P_1(0) = 0 and the above normalization this gives P_1(x) = x, so the first row is 1.
%C A393943 The coefficients in each row and in each column strictly alternate in sign.
%C A393943 T(n, k) is the primitive integer normalization of A008276(n, k)/k. Proof: Let P_n'(x) = Product_{j=1..n-1} (x - j). Using the identity Product_{j=0..n-1} (x - j) = Sum_{k=0..n} A008276(n, k) x^k, we obtain P_n'(x) = Sum_{k=1..n} A008276(n, k) x^(k-1). Integrating and using P_n(0) = 0 gives P_n(x) = Sum_{k=1..n} (A008276(n, k)/k) x^k. Thus the coefficients are proportional to A008276(n, k)/k.
%C A393943 Proof of the edge formulas: (Start)
%C A393943 We have T(n,k) = primitive integer normalization of A008276(n, k)/k. Hence there exists a constant C_n such that T(n, k) = C_n*A008276(n, k)/k. The constant C_n is determined by clearing denominators, i.e., for every prime p, v_p(C_n) = - min_{1<=k<=n} v_p(A008276(n, k)/k).
%C A393943 Now, v_p(A008276(n, k)/k) = v_p(A008276(n, k)) - v_p(k). Results on the p-adic valuations of Stirling numbers of the first kind (see e.g. Adelberg, Acta Arith. 1990; Lengyel, Fibonacci Quart. 1994) imply that the minimum over k occurs at k = p^m (for suitable m), and that min_{1<=k<=n} v_p(A008276(n, k)/k) = - floor((n - 1)/(p - 1)). Hence v_p(C_n) = floor((n - 1)/(p - 1)), so C_n = Product_{p<=n} p^floor((n - 1)/(p - 1)) = A091137(n - 1).
%C A393943 Right edge: Since A008276(n, n) = 1, T(n, n) = C_n/n = A091137(n - 1)/n = A363596(n - 1).
%C A393943 Left edge: Since A008276(n, 1) = (-1)^(n - 1)*(n -  1)!, T(n, 1) = C_n*(-1)^(n - 1)*(n - 1)! = (-1)^(n - 1)*(n - 1)!*A091137(n - 1). (end)
%D A393943 A. Adelberg, p-adic valuations of Stirling numbers of the first kind, Acta Arith., 56 (1990), 51-60.
%D A393943 T. Lengyel, On the divisibility by p of Stirling numbers of the first kind, Fibonacci Quart., 32 (1994), 194-201.
%H A393943 Felix Huber, <a href="/A393943/b393943.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10011 (rows 1 to 141, flattened)</a>
%F A393943 T(n,k) = (A003418(n)/g(n)) * A008277(n,k) / k, where g(n) = gcd_{1<=k<=n} (A003418(n)*A008277(n,k)/k).
%F A393943 T(n, n) = A363596(n - 1).
%F A393943 T(n, 1) = A033999(n - 1) * A091137(n - 1).
%e A393943 The Triangle T(n, k) begins:
%e A393943   n\k       1         2         3         4         5         6         7         8         9
%e A393943   1         1
%e A393943   2        -2         1
%e A393943   3        12        -9         2
%e A393943   4       -24        22        -8         1
%e A393943   5       720      -750       350       -75         6
%e A393943   6     -1440      1644      -900       255       -36         2
%e A393943   7     60480    -74088     45472    -15435      2940      -294        12
%e A393943   8   -120960    156816   -105056     40614     -9408      1288       -96         3
%e A393943   9   3628800  -4931280   3543720  -1513890    404082    -68040      7020      -405        10
%e A393943 P_3(x) = 12*x - 9*x^2 + 2*x^3, P_3'(x) = 12 - 18*x + 6*x^2 = 6*(x - 1)*(x - 2) with zeros 1 and 2.
%p A393943 T := proc(n, k) option remember;
%p A393943     local l, v, g, i;
%p A393943     l := ilcm(seq(i, i = 1 .. n));
%p A393943     v := [seq(l*combinat:-stirling1(n, i)/i, i = 1 .. n)];
%p A393943     g := igcd(op(v));
%p A393943     v[k]/g;
%p A393943 end proc:
%p A393943 seq(seq(T(n, k), k = 1 .. n), n = 1 .. 9);
%Y A393943 Cf. A003418, A008276, A033999, A091137, A363596, A373995, A373996, A373997.
%K A393943 sign,tabl,easy,new
%O A393943 1,2
